<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-152-027 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 758 417</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  May 20 1991 v140 pC8(N) pD8(L) 7 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Companies in Apple suit pessimistic on settling. (Apple ComputerInc.'s copyright lawsuit against Microsoft Corp. and HewlettPackard Co.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pollack, Andrew.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple Computer Inc's copyright lawsuit against HP and MicrosoftCorp is not expected to reach a settlement, and the law suit mightnot come to trial until some time in 1993.andP;  The lawsuit, whichbegan in Mar 1988, alleges that the Microsoft Windows 2.03graphical user interface and the HP NewWave program infringe onthe copyrighted screen display of the Apple Macintosh.andP;  Apple'sscreen display is a major selling point for its Macintosh line ofmicrocomputers because it makes the computer easier to use thanthe competition.andP;  Industry observers note that Apple, which ispushing to get the law suit to trial by Jan 1992, will add thepopular Microsoft Windows 3.0 graphical user interface to thelawsuit.andP;  Microsoft and HP are motioning to get the entire lawsuitdismissed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Cases)Microsoft Corp. (Cases)Hewlett-Packard Co. (Cases).andO;Ticker:    MSFT; AAPL; HWP.andO;Topic:     Software PublishersLaw SuitCopyrightIntellectual propertyLegal Issues.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>